  "text": "In both [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] , the counting experiments are performed in simulation, with no human operator involved. This paper proposes an algorithm that allows an operator to select any robot from a group of real robots, and receive a count of the robots which are in communication range. Subsequently the operator can manage the group of robots by assigning different tasks to subgroups of them, and then releasing them to perform the tasks.",
